28/08/2009
ANKARA, Turkey -- Five people died and 21 were injured Thursday (August 27th) after a passenger express train hit a road construction vehicle trying to cross the tracks.
One of the train carriages overturned as a result of the collision and three others derailed.
It happened in Bilecik province in northwest Turkey.
The train was travelling from Eskisehir to Istanbul.
(Hurriyet, Milliyet, Cumhurriyet - 28/08/09;
Reuters, Anadolu news agency - 27/08/09)
